# Component size limits

## Hard limit

- **UI component files** (`*.tsx` / `*.jsx`) must stay **≤ 100 lines** (count includes imports and exports).
- **`page.tsx` / `layout.tsx`** must stay **≤ 40 lines** — orchestration only; render imported components.

If a file exceeds the limit, **stop adding to it** and split before continuing.

## How to split (no bunching, no over-chunking)

**Bunching (avoid):** multiple components, hooks, fetch logic, types, and large constant maps in one file.

**Over-chunking (avoid):** splitting a < 80-line component into many 10-line files with no clear boundary.

| Extract when… | Into… |
|---|---|
| Reusable UI block (header, toolbar, row, panel) | `./component-name-part.tsx` in the same folder |
| State, effects, handlers | `./use-component-name.ts` |
| Types / props interfaces | `./component-name.types.ts` |
| Static options, nav items, maps | `./component-name.config.ts` |
| Non-trivial Tailwind/CSS (> ~25 lines) | Colocated `./component-name.css` |

Folder example:

```
blueprints/
  blueprint-composer.tsx        # ≤ 100 lines, composes subparts
  blueprint-composer.css
  use-composer-textarea.ts
  blueprint-attach-menu.tsx
```

## Review checklist before finishing a UI change

- [ ] No file over 100 lines (pages over 40)
- [ ] One primary exported component per file
- [ ] No inline subcomponents nested more than one level deep — extract instead
- [ ] Shared logic in hooks/utils, not duplicated across components
